       "The car is registered in my name."
       "The house is in my wife's name."
     2) именем (using the authority of sb/sth; as a representative of sb/sth)
       "I arrest you in the name of the law."
       "They were arrested in the name of the king."
       "As members of the union, we have the right to know what action the union is taking in our name."
     3) ради, во имя (used to give a reason or an excuse for doing sth, often when what you are doing is wrong)
       "crimes committed in the name of religion"

